Adamawa State government has approved N656 million for the purchase of fertilizer and other agro-chemicals for this year’s farming season. The approval was disclosed Wednesday in Yola by Dr Umar Garba-Pella, Commissioner for Information and Strategy, shortly after state Executive Council meeting. Pella said agricultural diversification remains top priority and therefore N550 was appropriated for purchase of fertilizer, while over   N106 million  was also approved for the  purchase of assorted agrochemicals and hybrid seeds for disbursement to farmers. He said the state ministry of Agriculture would oversee the sales of the  fertilizer to  farmers at a subsidize price  of N5,500  per bag of 50  kg of NPK less than  market price in the state. The N106 million would be used to buy 50,000 assorted agro-chemicals,  hybrid seeds to boost food security, The Commissioner attributed  delayed in  the process procuring the fertilizer to security situation on the commodity  in the North eastern states by the federal government on security ground. The development followed  government request to  federal government through the office of the National Security Adviser to lift the ban on  NPK fertilizer in the north east, otherwise government has no option than to look for any satisfied product for purchase. Dr Dishi Khobe, Commissioner for Agriculture said the  supply of fertilizer to the state is timely as only targeted beneficiaries would  benefit from the gesture. Meanwhile, Dr Edgar Amos  Head of Civil Service hinted that, the state would soon commence Pension Contributory Scheme as the current pension scheme is marred  with a lot of challenges. 